dsiter.operator

Class TypedBinaryOperator

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsiter.operator.TypedBinaryOperator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRowAccessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AndOperator, CaretOperator, DivideOperator, EqualsOperator, GreaterThanEqualsOperator, GreaterThanOperator, LessThanEqualsOperator, LessThanOperator, MinusOperator, ModuloOperator, NthRootOperator, OrOperator, PlusOperator, TimesOperator

    public abstract class TypedBinaryOperator
extends java.lang.Object
implements IRowAccessor
    Abstract class for use in creating binary operators. Not all binary operators need to use this class, but it's almost certainly easier to implement if you do.

    Subclasses must override the getReturnType(dsiter.row.ColumnType, dsiter.row.ColumnType) and testTypeCompatibility(dsiter.row.ColumnType, dsiter.row.ColumnType) methods. This class can then use that information to determine how best to process the child operators.

    This class provides overrideable methods for every possible type combination of lhs, rhs, and returnValue (which means there are (# of types)^3 overridable methods available). Subclasses only need to override the methods which they will actually support. So, for example, a logical boolean operator only needs to override handle_boolean_boolean_boolean(boolean, boolean) and a numeric operator will only need to override the appropriate numeric handle_x_y_z methods. This superclass will use the information from getReturnType(dsiter.row.ColumnType, dsiter.row.ColumnType) and testTypeCompatibility(dsiter.row.ColumnType, dsiter.row.ColumnType) to efficiently determine which method to call.
